        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 23 at 7:50PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 750 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Detroit, or 11 miles northwest of Sulligent, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tucker, Detroit, Henson Springs, Bazemore, Wayside, Winfield, Rankin
Fite Airport, Twin, Brilliant, Guin, Gu-
Win, Hubbertville, Texas, Byrd, Beaverton, Pine Springs, Crews,
Marion County Public Lake, Glen Allen, and Piney Grove.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight CDT for
central, northwestern and west central Alabama.</instruction>
